member.name: P:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.ImagingTools.Info.PixXDim
member.summary: Type is PropertyTagTypeShort or PropertyTagTypeLong Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid width of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag, whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should not exist in an uncompressed file.

member.name: P:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.ImagingTools.Info.PixYDim
member.summary: Type is PropertyTagTypeShort or PropertyTagTypeLong Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid height of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should not exist in an uncompressed file. Because data padding is unnecessary in the vertical direction, the number of lines recorded in this valid image height tag will be the same as that recorded in the SOF.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.Unloading
member.summary: The page is unloading. This flag is set in response to the onbeforeunload and onunload events. Some pages load pop-up windows when you leave them rather than when you enter. This flag is used to identify those situations.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.UserInited
member.summary: The call to INewWindowManager::EvaluateNewWindow is the result of a user-initiated action (a mouse click or key press). Use this flag in conjunction with the NWMF_FIRST_USERINITED flag to determine whether the call is a direct or indirect result of the user-initiated action.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.UserFirstInited
member.summary: When NWMF_USERINITED is present, this flag indicates that the call to INewWindowManager::EvaluateNewWindow is the first query that results from this user-initiated action. Always use this flag in conjunction with NWMF_USERINITED.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.OverrideKey
member.summary: The override key (ALT) was pressed. The override key is used to bypass the pop-up manager�allowing all pop-up windows to display�and must be held down at the time that INewWindowManager::EvaluateNewWindow is called.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.ShowHelp
member.summary: The new window attempting to load is the result of a call to the showHelp method. Help is sometimes displayed in a separate window, and this flag is valuable in those cases.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.HtmlDialog
member.summary: The new window is a dialog box that displays HTML content.

member.name: F:BalfoursBusinessClassLibrary.UrlContext.FromProxy
member.summary: Indicates that the EvaluateNewWindow method is being called through a marshalled Component Object Model (COM) proxy from another thread. In this situation, the method should make a decision and return immediately without performing blocking operations such as showing modal user interface (UI). Lengthy operations will cause the calling thread to appear unresponsive.
